00:00:01.033 --> 00:00:04.100
♪♪

00:00:05.133 --> 00:00:08.167
Narrator: A DRY-ERASE BOARD
IS A NONPERMANENT SURFACE

00:00:08.167 --> 00:00:10.067
MOST COMMONLY USED
IN PROFESSIONAL

00:00:10.067 --> 00:00:11.934
OR CLASSROOM ENVIRONMENTS.

00:00:11.934 --> 00:00:14.801
YOU SIMPLY WRITE ON THE BOARD
WITH A DRY-ERASE MARKER

00:00:14.801 --> 00:00:18.868
AND USE A SPECIALIZED CLOTH
TO WIPE AWAY THE MARKINGS.

00:00:18.868 --> 00:00:21.000
THESE EFFECTIVE TOOLS
ARE AN EASY WAY

00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:23.334
TO GET YOUR MESSAGE ACROSS.

00:00:24.501 --> 00:00:27.767
DRY-ERASE BOARDS ARE ALSO
KNOWN AS WHITEBOARDS.

00:00:29.567 --> 00:00:31.400
THE BOARDS WIPE PERFECTLY CLEAN

00:00:31.400 --> 00:00:36.400
DUE TO ITS NONPOROUS SURFACE
AND THE DRY-ERASE INK.

00:00:36.400 --> 00:00:39.067
DRY-ERASE INK CONTAINS
RELEASE AGENTS

00:00:39.067 --> 00:00:40.334
WHICH PREVENT THE PIGMENTS

00:00:40.334 --> 00:00:44.267
FROM PERMANENTLY
ADHERING TO THE SURFACE.

00:00:44.267 --> 00:00:48.567
GREEN AND BLACK DRY-ERASE BOARDS
CAN ALSO BE USED AS CHALKBOARDS,

00:00:48.567 --> 00:00:53.434
WHILE GRAY AND LOW-GLOSS WHITE
DOUBLE AS PROJECTION BOARDS.

00:00:53.434 --> 00:00:57.067
THE SURFACE MATERIAL IS A
PORCELAIN-COATED STEEL SHEET --

00:00:57.067 --> 00:01:01.167
FLEXIBLE ENOUGH TO BE ROLLED UP,
BUT ALSO PRESSURE SENSITIVE.

00:01:01.167 --> 00:01:03.267
♪♪

00:01:03.267 --> 00:01:07.000
TO START, THE ROLL IS MOUNTED
ON A CUTTING MACHINE.

00:01:07.000 --> 00:01:09.100
♪♪

00:01:09.100 --> 00:01:12.200
A TECHNICIAN PROGRAMS
THE MACHINE TO CUT THE ROLL

00:01:12.200 --> 00:01:17.834
TO A SPECIFIC LENGTH
BASED ON THE BOARD'S DIMENSIONS.

00:01:17.834 --> 00:01:22.968
WORKERS VERIFY THE LENGTH AND
CHECK THAT THE PIECE IS SQUARE.

00:01:22.968 --> 00:01:25.033
THE SURFACE MATERIAL
WILL BE APPLIED

00:01:25.033 --> 00:01:27.467
TO ONE OF SEVEN TYPES
OF SUBSTRATE,

00:01:27.467 --> 00:01:29.334
RANGING FROM CARDBOARD

00:01:29.334 --> 00:01:34.767
TO MEDIUM-DENSITY FIBERBOARD
KNOWN AS MDF.

00:01:34.767 --> 00:01:37.901
THE NEXT STEP IS TO CUT
THE LARGE SHEET OF SUBSTRATE --

00:01:37.901 --> 00:01:41.801
IN THIS CASE, MDF --
INTO BOARD-SIZE PIECES.

00:01:41.801 --> 00:01:44.200
ANOTHER TECHNICIAN
ENTERS THE LENGTH AND WIDTH

00:01:44.200 --> 00:01:46.367
INTO THE CUTTING MACHINE.

00:01:46.367 --> 00:01:50.000
♪♪

00:01:50.000 --> 00:01:53.334
ONCE COMPLETE, THE MACHINE
EJECTS THE SUBSTRATE,

00:01:53.334 --> 00:01:57.067
WHICH IS NOW CUT
TO THE EXACT SIZE OF THE BOARD.

00:01:57.067 --> 00:02:01.834
♪♪

00:02:01.834 --> 00:02:05.501
NEXT, THE SUBSTRATE IS PUT
THROUGH A HOT-GLUE MACHINE.

00:02:05.501 --> 00:02:08.167
THE MACHINE APPLIES
POLYURETHANE ADHESIVE

00:02:08.167 --> 00:02:13.000
TO WHAT WILL BE THE BACK
OF THE DRY-ERASE BOARD.

00:02:13.000 --> 00:02:15.033
AS THE SUBSTRATE EXITS,

00:02:15.033 --> 00:02:19.133
A SHEET OF FOIL
IS APPLIED TO THE GLUED SURFACE.

00:02:19.133 --> 00:02:21.601
THE FOIL PREVENTS MOISTURE
FROM ENTERING,

00:02:21.601 --> 00:02:24.501
WHICH WOULD WARP THE SUBSTRATE.

00:02:24.501 --> 00:02:26.901
THE BOARD MOVES THROUGH
TWO STEEL ROLLERS

00:02:26.901 --> 00:02:31.934
WHICH FLATTEN THE FOIL
AND PRESS OUT ANY TRAPPED AIR.

00:02:31.934 --> 00:02:34.334
NEXT, THE SURFACE MATERIAL
IS APPLIED

00:02:34.334 --> 00:02:38.167
TO THE OTHER SIDE
OF THE SUBSTRATE.

00:02:38.167 --> 00:02:41.868
A CRAFTSWOMAN USES AN AIR HOSE
TO CLEAR AWAY ANY DUST

00:02:41.868 --> 00:02:43.868
FROM THE SIDE OF THE BOARD.

00:02:43.868 --> 00:02:48.400
ONCE CLEANED, THE BOARD
GOES THROUGH THE GLUE MACHINE.

00:02:48.400 --> 00:02:52.367
THE PORCELAIN STEEL SHEET
IS PLACED ON THE GLUED SURFACE.

00:02:52.367 --> 00:02:55.434
TECHNICIANS WORK CAREFULLY
TO ENSURE THEY DON'T TOUCH

00:02:55.434 --> 00:02:59.234
THE PRESSURE-SENSITIVE SURFACE
WITH THEIR FINGERS.

00:02:59.234 --> 00:03:01.901
THEN THE BOARD MOVES
THROUGH THE STEEL ROLLERS

00:03:01.901 --> 00:03:06.267
TO PRESS THE PORCELAIN STEEL
FLAT AND REMOVE ANY TRAPPED AIR.

00:03:06.267 --> 00:03:11.601
♪♪

00:03:11.601 --> 00:03:15.167
ONCE 50 BOARDS ARE STACKED,
TECHNICIANS PUT THEM IN A PRESS

00:03:15.167 --> 00:03:18.501
FOR HALF AN HOUR,
UNTIL THE GLUE CURES.

00:03:18.501 --> 00:03:23.701
♪♪

00:03:23.701 --> 00:03:28.901
♪♪

00:03:28.901 --> 00:03:32.033
IN ANOTHER PART OF THE FACTORY,
A MACHINE CUTS MATERIAL

00:03:32.033 --> 00:03:34.100
TO CREATE THE BOARD'S FRAME.

00:03:34.100 --> 00:03:39.067
IT PUNCHES "V"-SHAPED NOTCHES
IN THE LENGTH OF ALUMINUM TRIM.

00:03:39.067 --> 00:03:43.501
THE TRIM BENDS AT EACH NOTCH
TO FORM A WRAPAROUND FRAME.

00:03:43.501 --> 00:03:47.968
♪♪

00:03:47.968 --> 00:03:52.200
SOME BOARDS COME WITH A MARKER
TRAY THAT RUNS ALONG THE BOTTOM.

00:03:52.200 --> 00:03:53.601
TO MAKE THESE TRAYS,

00:03:53.601 --> 00:03:55.634
A TECHNICIAN CUTS
BOARD-LENGTH PIECES

00:03:55.634 --> 00:03:58.767
FROM A PIECE
OF "L"-SHAPED METAL TRIM.

00:03:58.767 --> 00:04:02.934
♪♪

00:04:02.934 --> 00:04:04.934
SINCE THE TRAY ENDS ARE SHARP,

00:04:04.934 --> 00:04:09.000
A TECHNICIAN ATTACHES
PLASTIC COVERS FOR PROTECTION.

00:04:09.000 --> 00:04:11.000
♪♪

00:04:11.000 --> 00:04:13.534
HE SECURES THE PLASTIC
END COVERS WITH SCREWS

00:04:13.534 --> 00:04:15.968
ON BOTH ENDS OF THE PART.

00:04:15.968 --> 00:04:20.734
♪♪

00:04:20.734 --> 00:04:24.100
MEANWHILE, TECHNICIANS
PEEL OFF THE PROTECTIVE FILM

00:04:24.100 --> 00:04:26.801
COVERING THE WRITING SURFACE.

00:04:26.801 --> 00:04:30.434
♪♪

00:04:30.434 --> 00:04:32.000
THEN THEY FLIP OVER THE BOARD

00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:34.734
TO ASSEMBLE THE PARTS
FROM THE BACK.

00:04:34.734 --> 00:04:36.801
♪♪

00:04:36.801 --> 00:04:40.300
THIS MODEL DOESN'T HAVE THE
TRADITIONAL WRAPAROUND FRAME.

00:04:40.300 --> 00:04:42.133
INSTEAD, IT HAS A FRAME

00:04:42.133 --> 00:04:45.367
COMPRISED OF FOUR STRAIGHT
"C"-SHAPED PIECES

00:04:45.367 --> 00:04:49.334
THAT FIT OVER THE BOARD'S EDGES.

00:04:49.334 --> 00:04:52.367
TO ADD STABILITY,
TECHNICIANS ATTACH SCREWS

00:04:52.367 --> 00:04:55.167
THROUGH THE TRIM
INTO THE SUBSTRATE.

00:04:55.167 --> 00:04:57.133
♪♪

00:04:57.133 --> 00:04:58.868
ONCE ASSEMBLY IS COMPLETE,

00:04:58.868 --> 00:05:02.534
THE DRY-ERASE BOARD
IS PLACED INTO A BOX,

00:05:02.534 --> 00:05:06.501
READY TO BE SHIPPED TO A
BUSINESS OR CLASSROOM NEAR YOU.

